The Deiyai Parliament has called for the officers involved to be held to account and for the mobile police brigade to be withdrawn from the area.
Paniai has always been a source of trouble for the Indonesian government.
The lack of meaningful development is fuelling the discontent of the Mee, Moni, Dani and Damal tribes living in the green highlands of Papua.
